About this Exercise Let us try some packages to manipulate and forecast time series data. # What we want to do We want to find the most suitable package(s) that can: 1. allow us to easily aggregate daily data to monthly data 2. impute missing values 3. do decomposition of time series data 4. plot time series data 5. do forecasting of time series data # Getting Started ## Installing and launching the packages ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} pacman::p_load(tidyverse, lubridate, DT, ggplot2, plotly, ggthemes, timetk, modeltime, tidymodels, xgboost, recipes, parsnip, earth) ``` ::: ## Importing the data We use `read_csv()` function of **readr** to import the `daily_historical` csv file into R then we will use `glimpse()` of **dplyr** to learn about the associated attribute information in the dataframe. ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code code-fold="true" code-summary="Show the code"} data <- read_csv("data/daily_historical.csv") glimpse(data) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` Rows: ``` ::: ::: # Forecasting with Modeltime Going to develop a few basic models - ARIMA - Exponential Smoothing - Linear Regression - MARS (Multivariate Adaptive Regression Splines) ## Selecting the data We use mean monthly temperature of Admiralty station as an example. First we will select the relevant data column ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} glimpse(weatherdata) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` Rows: 1,548 Columns: 6 Groups: station [13] $ station "Admiralty", "Admiralty", "Admiralty", "Admir… $ DATE 2014-01-01, 2014-02-01, 2014-03-01, 2014-04-… $ mean_monthly_temperature 26.22903, 25.79355, 26.76071, 27.35484, 27.81… $ min_monthly_temperature 21.70000, 22.40000, 21.80000, 23.50000, 22.40… $ max_monthly_temperature 25.30000, 24.90000, 24.90000, 25.80000, 26.50… $ monthly_rainfall 98.8000, 15.8000, 120.0000, 261.4000, 301.000… ``` ::: ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} weatherdata_meantemp <- weatherdata %>% filter(station == "Admiralty") %>% select(date = DATE, value = mean_monthly_temperature) weatherdata_meantemp ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` # A tibble: 119 × 3 # Groups: station [1] station date value 1 Admiralty 2014-01-01 26.2 2 Admiralty 2014-02-01 25.8 3 Admiralty 2014-03-01 26.8 4 Admiralty 2014-04-01 27.4 5 Admiralty 2014-05-01 27.8 6 Admiralty 2014-06-01 28.2 7 Admiralty 2014-07-01 28.9 8 Admiralty 2014-08-01 28.6 9 Admiralty 2014-09-01 28.0 10 Admiralty 2014-11-01 27.8 # ℹ 109 more rows ``` ::: ::: ## Visualise the dataset ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} weatherdata_meantemp %>% plot_time_series(date, value) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ## Train/Test ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} splits <- weatherdata_meantemp %>% initial_time_split(prop = 0.8) splits ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` <95/24/119> ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} training(splits) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` # A tibble: 95 × 3 # Groups: station [1] station date value 1 Admiralty 2014-01-01 26.2 2 Admiralty 2014-02-01 25.8 3 Admiralty 2014-03-01 26.8 4 Admiralty 2014-04-01 27.4 5 Admiralty 2014-05-01 27.8 6 Admiralty 2014-06-01 28.2 7 Admiralty 2014-07-01 28.9 8 Admiralty 2014-08-01 28.6 9 Admiralty 2014-09-01 28.0 10 Admiralty 2014-11-01 27.8 # ℹ 85 more rows ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} testing(splits) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` # A tibble: 24 × 3 # Groups: station [1] station date value 1 Admiralty 2022-01-01 27.2 2 Admiralty 2022-02-01 27.0 3 Admiralty 2022-03-01 26.8 4 Admiralty 2022-04-01 27.7 5 Admiralty 2022-05-01 27.7 6 Admiralty 2022-06-01 28.8 7 Admiralty 2022-07-01 27.5 8 Admiralty 2022-08-01 28.4 9 Admiralty 2022-09-01 27.6 10 Admiralty 2022-10-01 27.5 # ℹ 14 more rows ``` ::: ::: ## Creating and Fitting Models ### Model 1 - Auto ARIMA ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} model_fit_arima_no_boost <- arima_reg() %>% set_engine(engine = "auto_arima") %>% fit(value ~ date, data = training(splits)) ``` ::: ### Boosted Auto ARIMA Create a boosted ARIMA. Boosting uses XGBOost to model the ARIMA errors. ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} model_fit_arima_boosted <- arima_boost( min_n = 2, learn_rate = 0.015 ) %>% set_engine(engine = "auto_arima_xgboost") %>% fit(value ~ date + as.numeric(date) + factor(month(date, label = TRUE), ordered = F), data = training(splits)) ``` ::: ### Exponential Smoothing ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} model_fit_ets <- exp_smoothing() %>% set_engine(engine = "ets") %>% fit(value ~ date, data = training(splits)) ``` ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} model_fit_ets ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` parsnip model object ETS(A,N,A) Call: forecast::ets(y = outcome, model = model_ets, damped = damping_ets, Call: alpha = alpha, beta = beta, gamma = gamma) Smoothing parameters: alpha = 0.3744 gamma = 1e-04 Initial states: l = 27.4844 s = -0.853 -0.4341 0.2104 0.2587 0.5635 0.6531 0.3323 0.5585 0.3482 0.0175 -0.7688 -0.8861 sigma: 0.4493 AIC AICc BIC 295.4710 301.5470 333.7792 ``` ::: ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} calibration_ets <- model_fit_ets %>% modeltime_calibrate(new_data = testing(splits)) calibration_ets ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` # Modeltime Table # A tibble: 1 × 5 .model_id .model .model_desc .type .calibration_data 1 1 ETS(A,N,A) Test ``` ::: ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} forecast_results <- calibration_ets %>% modeltime_forecast( new_data = testing(splits), actual_data = weatherdata_meantemp ) datatable(forecast_results) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} calibration_ets %>% modeltime_forecast( new_data = testing(splits), actual_data = weatherdata_meantemp ) %>% plot_modeltime_forecast( .legend_max_width = 25 ) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ### Accuracy Metrics ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} accuracy_metrics <- calibration_ets %>% modeltime_accuracy() accuracy_metrics$mae ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` [1] 0.4177054 ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} accuracy_metrics$mape ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` [1] 1.510336 ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} accuracy_metrics$rmse ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` [1] 0.5062106 ``` ::: ::: ### Prophet ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} model_fit_prophet <- prophet_reg() %>% set_engine(engine = "prophet") %>% fit(value ~ date, data = training(splits)) ``` ::: ### Linear Regression ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} model_fit_lm <- linear_reg() %>% set_engine("lm") %>% fit(value ~ as.numeric(date) + factor(month(date, label = TRUE), ordered = FALSE), data = training(splits)) ``` ::: ### MARS ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} model_spec_mars <- mars(mode = "regression") %>% set_engine("earth") recipe_spec <- recipe(value ~ date, data = training(splits)) %>% step_date(date, features = "month", ordinal = FALSE) %>% step_mutate(date_num = as.numeric(date)) %>% step_normalize(date_num) %>% step_rm(date) wflw_fit_mars <- workflow() %>% add_recipe(recipe_spec) %>% add_model(model_spec_mars) %>% fit(training(splits)) ``` ::: ## Add Fitted Models to a Model table ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} models_tbl <- modeltime_table( model_fit_arima_no_boost, model_fit_arima_boosted, model_fit_ets, model_fit_prophet, model_fit_lm, wflw_fit_mars ) models_tbl ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` # Modeltime Table # A tibble: 6 × 3 .model_id .model .model_desc 1 1 ARIMA(1,0,0)(2,1,0)[12] 2 2 ARIMA(1,0,0)(2,1,0)[12] W/ XGBOOST ERRORS 3 3 ETS(A,N,A) 4 4 PROPHET 5 5 LM 6 6 EARTH ``` ::: ::: ## Calibrate the model to a testing set ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} calibration_tbl <- models_tbl %>% modeltime_calibrate(new_data = testing(splits)) calibration_tbl ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` # Modeltime Table # A tibble: 6 × 5 .model_id .model .model_desc .type .calibration_data 1 1 ARIMA(1,0,0)(2,1,0)[12] Test 2 2 ARIMA(1,0,0)(2,1,0)[12] W/ XGBOO… Test 3 3 ETS(A,N,A) Test 4 4 PROPHET Test 5 5 LM Test 6 6 EARTH Test ``` ::: ::: ## Testing Set Forecast & Accuracy Evaluation ### visualising forecast test ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} calibration_tbl %>% modeltime_forecast( new_data = testing(splits), actual_data = weatherdata_meantemp ) %>% plot_modeltime_forecast( .legend_max_width = 25 ) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ### Accuracy Metrics ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} calibration_tbl %>% modeltime_accuracy() %>% table_modeltime_accuracy() ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
